glosses: An academic grade used in Finnish abitur and university theses, the second highest pass grade.
categories: Finnish terms with redundant head parameter

words.etymology_text: From Latin, "someone or something is approved with excellent praise".

glosses: Short for eximia cum laude approbatur (the second highest grade in Finnish baccalaureate exams)
